    <string name="info_title">About Halal Scanner</string>
    <string name="info_msg">This app checks products for halal status in two ways:\n\n• Barcode scan fetches product info from OpenFoodFacts\n• OCR scan reads the ingredient list directly from packaging — works for any product\n\nIngredients are matched against a database of known haram (pork, alcohol, carmine/E120, shellac/E904, L-cysteine/E920, …) and mushbooh (doubtful: gelatin, mono-/diglycerides E471-E479, bone phosphate E542, natural flavors, glycerin E422, …) substances.\n\nIMPORTANT: This is NOT a fatwa. It is based on the widely-held consensus of Islamic dietary law. When in doubt, choose a certified halal product.</string>

